const faqs = [
  {
    q: "My wine cellar is at 50% humidity. Is that low enough to damage inventory?",
    a: "50% RH is borderline. Wine cork preservation typically targets 55 to 70% RH. Below 50% extended periods causes corks to dry, shrink, and allow oxygen ingress. Above 80% RH causes label damage and mold risk. Target the middle of 55 to 65% for most cellars. We diagnose humidity drift causes including drain reroute, defrost imbalance, and supplemental humidifier failure."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Wine Guardian and CellarPro?",
    a: "Yes. These are our two most common premium wine cellar brands in LA, OC, and Ventura restaurant cellars. Wine Guardian D-Series ducted splits and CellarPro 4200 self-contained units are the most frequent service calls. We carry common evaporator fan motors and humidity components for both lines."
  },
  {
    q: "My multi-zone wine room has one zone drifting. Is that the whole system?",
    a: "Probably not. Multi-zone systems have separate thermostats per zone. One zone drifting equals that zone's thermostat needs recalibration or replacement. Other zones are likely fine. We diagnose per zone rather than assuming a whole-system failure, and we recalibrate against zone-specific spec (red 55 to 58°F, white 50 to 55°F, sparkling 45 to 50°F)."
  },
  {
    q: "How urgent is wine cellar cooling failure?",
    a: "Depends on the inventory and the failure mode. Cellar at 65°F for 24 hours: limited damage to most inventory. Cellar at 75°F+ for several days: serious damage to age-worthy wine. Cellar at 80°F+ ever: stop-the-line emergency. We dispatch accordingly and document temperature/humidity recovery for insurance purposes."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you work with my sommelier on the diagnosis?",
    a: "Yes. We routinely coordinate with sommeliers, beverage directors, and wine program managers. They know which inventory is most temperature-sensitive, where the staff has been observing issues, and what the wine program priorities are. Coordinating directly with the wine program saves diagnostic time and protects inventory."
  },
  {
    q: "My wine cellar uses R-454B. What's that?",
    a: "R-454B is a newer green refrigerant (replacing R-410A) used in some 2024+ Wine Guardian and CellarPro models. Different service procedures than R-410A: lower GWP, mildly flammable A2L classification, requires specific tools and recovery equipment. Requires R-454B-ready service training. We have it."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor warranty on every repair. Component manufacturer warranties (Wine Guardian, CellarPro, KoolR) processed separately through the manufacturer's authorized network. EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410). BHGS #A49573. BBB A+ accredited."
  }
];

